tip.text: Serious looking coffee equipment and handsome, helpful baristas in this quiet take away shop. Single origin beans, a deep roast, brewed slowly, made a wonderful coffee with a powerful kick. Yum!
Great ambiance for special night out in Florence. Book ahead. Recommend: asparagus and mushroom risotto, good house wine as well.

location.crossStreet: Piazza Salvemini / Arco Di San Piero
formattedAddress: Borgo Pinti 10/12/14/18/R (Piazza Salvemini / Arco Di San Piero)

tip.text: My favorite bridge, beautiful views both ways including looking at the next bridge Ponte Vecchio. Less crowded, and a great view of sunset on the water.
Lovely hotel, a bit dated architecture, but a very nice staff keeps you happy.

contact.facebookName: Regent Singapore, A Four Seasons Hotel

tip.text: Super cool concept... Fun interior design. The desserts are massive... Bring a friend to finish one.

Healthy vegetarian options with calorie counts on menu... Love it.. Very NYC. Super fresh and clean, and very flavorful options. I am coming back and bringing friends. Recommend: pumpkin barley drink.
Love this place. Yes... It is hard to know at first glance if it's as night club or airport lounge... But any lounge with an entire wall of food dedicated to vegetarians is top in my book.

contact.facebookName: Eva Air Vip Lounge - the Infinity

tip.text: The name might lead you to think Chinese food, but it's all western fare here. Humongous beers on tap, and a great indoor/outdoor corner location to people watch.
In the mood for super decadent? You may pass out from the intensity, but they serve  Stumptown coffee to jump start your heart. Recommend: Brooklyn Blackout cake & chocolate salted caramel cupcake
Beautiful theater with busy but decent bathroom at intermission. Comfy seats.
Recommend: red velvet cake is very solid with good frosting, and key lime pie is less sweet with a nice zing.
Hip little cafe focused on matcha. Recommend: matcha coconut macaroon with chocolate base, and the Fuji Apple Ginger Matcha cold drink. Refreshing and healthy...yum!
Really good beer flight. For a change of pace,  Recommend cask beer options. Half the carbonation leaves them a bit flat , but also smooth and flavorful. Great staff!
Purple-y, sweet, tangy, yummy goodness... Yes it's a Hibiscus Donut.
Very cool speakeasy in NYC tradition. Very handsome bar staff takes care of you. Great cocktails, but ask, and they will make something not on the menu as well.
Not as high end as some of the more exclusive places nearby, but good music and decent cocktails.
Great spot for serious drinks... Strong and unique cocktails.
Raw, vegan. If that hasn't scared you off, then come try this cute cafe with insanely fresh food. Cheese from cashews, kimchee nori rolls, carrot ginger soup, zucchini lasagna all tasty. Serves beer.
A big bowl of goodness. This Taiwan chain provides soft tofu base and lots of sweet toppings.
Big flagship store, beautiful building in the old post office. Men's is on the top floor.
Decent fresh pho, good portion for money. Vegetarian mushroom tofu can come with veggie broth... Just request. Tip: that's tea in the metal thermos on each table.. Flavorful with sweet scent, try it!
Great art location just off federation square.

venue.name: The Ian Potter Centre: NGV Australia

tip.text: Impressive gallery space. Interesting permanent collection... High quality traveling exhibition like Warhol & WeiWei
Nice use of space with exposed brick and concrete, industrial cabinets and lighting at the back of the lobby creates an open plan,  but cozy breakfast or dinner spot.
Good options here include pasta dishes and salads. Lighter food than heavy classic Italian served down in Little Italy.
Pretty country club near the connection to Sentosa Island. Decent Chinese food -  nice place for a business team lunch.
Shopping not very good, few stores and not very practical items. Recommend.. Come at night and check out the colorful fountain in the piazza.
Great staff and easy location connected to office lobby. Limited seating.. Be ready to take away..
Ok food.. Not many vegetarian choices. Food is ok.. But try Nam Nam next door.

formattedAddress: #B1-46/47 Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Road)

tip.text: Vegetarian pho... Not rich broth... But fresh crunchy veggies make it tasty.

formattedAddress: #B1-46/47, Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Rd)

tip.text: Great local food cafe with solid coffee. Just tried an amazing sweet: croissant bread pudding... Get it warm. Lightly sweet, soft, with touch of cinnamon and maple.. Yum!
Ehm..."unique" is only description for this dusty antique shop/old bluegrass music/cupcake shop combo. Dense walnut cupcake with wax-like buttercream frosting seem made with the original antiques.
Great coffee options including Kyoto cold drip from Japan. Good snacks from hot soup to scones to macaroons. Very good looking baristas give great service.
Healthy food, less oily and salty than typical. Smaller portions at higher price but the ingredients are high quality. Recommend: hot tofu with brown rice penne pasta and green pesto with nuts.
Trendy coffee shop along the stairs above Sheung Wan area. Free WiFi. Good desserts.
Crowded working temple - check out both sides they feel quite different from each other.
One of the best coffee experiences I have ever had, 100% due to the staff. Great single origin beans, gracefully hand poured, they let you smell multiple beans, and share shots of different brews.
Like this place. Modern look and similar feel to other trendy 9th Ave spots. Food is ok, servers are handsome. Papaya salad is fresh and tangy, but fried tofu was dry, green curry not spicy enough.
Vegetarian recommendation: try the organic tofu pho, lighter and richer flavored broth than curry veggie soup, with great anoki mushrooms and pho flat noodles.
Quick Vietnamese style noodles for lunch and dinner. Vegetarian options. Most popular dishes are any of the signature noodle soups. Great staff and service.
Fun bar in a more lounge style setting than previous location. Great drag shows and handsome bartenders.
Amazing cocktails in a modern classy setting. Recommend: check out the drink menu, if nothing excites you, ask the bartender to make you one that's no longer on the menu. You will be happy you asked.
Decent dim sum served quickly by handsome servers. Vegetarian? Recommend the vegetarian combo, 1 piece of all the types in its own bamboo steamer. Ask for hot chili's and vinegar.

formattedAddress: 5 E Broadway (at Bowery and Chatham Square)

tip.text: The coffee shop for coffee fanatics. Single origin beans, locally roasted, prepared meticulously in different ways. I enjoy the filter pour over. Delicious sweet toast tastes of banana bread..yum!

location.address: Shop LG, The Centre Mark, 287-299 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: Shop LG, The Centre Mark, 287-299 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Omg.. Dumplings! Real quality. The vegetarian in a mix of green vegetables and mushroom... Local place... Chopsticks, vinegar, hot sauce, soy sauce, communal style on each table.
Fun local neighborhood bar. Cute bartenders and sweet fruity drinks. Well decorated for the holidays. Ask the bartender what his favorite drink to make is... And you will get something special!
Yes it looks like star trek or star wars from the lobby... Very future-chic! Flexible space for performances.
Wow.. Nice place, good food. Recommend: Dolsat rice dish in Clay pot with tofu. Very handsome waiter will mix it for you if you ask. Pair with a ginger soju for an extra kick.
Great food, excellent for business meeting or dates. More Afghanistan / Pakistan cuisine than Indian, eat with your hands using some delicious breads.

formattedAddress: ITC Grand Chola (63, Mount Rd, Guindy)

tip.text: Thai food... usually know for spicy fresh tastes of basil, chiles and curry... is watered down here to bland and  uninspired. With 10 other thai places with 10 minutes walk, skip this one.
Tasty and fresh Vietnamese food. Vegetarian options.. Including vegetarian pho. Recommend crab cakes. Fun environment, be prepared to wait for a seat.
Fresh and healthy options for breakfast lunch and dinner. Omelets are particularly good, are made fresh to order, with whole eggs or egg whites. Veggie panini is not worth it.
Local pizza in Monroe, medium crust thickness with good toppings. Recommend the basil pesto panini if you are not in the mood for pizza. Good service.
Food is not that great, coffee pretty weak. But clean and comfortable to sit of you are tired from shopping.

formattedAddress: #01-00, Jun Xin Building (402 North Bridge Road)

tip.text: Yum! They will rush you to eat so they can turn tables but the food is tasty. Recommend: clay pot dishes and noodles.
Disappointing coffee but decent sweets in a nice comfortable cafe with helpful and handsome staff to help make choices. The chocolate peanut butter banana layer cake is good option.
Clean hawker center with over 60 options including vegetarian choices. Most stalls give a good sized plate for about $3 to $4. Right next to the bedok MRT.
Fun cafe for a sweet treat and decent coffee.
Cool interactive art space built out of reclaimed shipping containers. Classes and group activities available.
Interesting shop with unique flavors. Basil and chocolate with tart fruit. Recommend: ice black coffee... Solid strong smooth.

formattedAddress: #02-01, School Of The Arts (1 Zubir Said Drive)

tip.text: Very nice bakery in Raffles hotel. Afternoon tea scone set is good, but it's not a proper scone. The texture is more like a big warm yummy buttermilk biscuit with raisins. Add flat white coffee.
Yummy sandwiches on crispy crust bread that makes you crave traditional Banh Mi.  Filled with current healthy / trendy vegetarian and meat options. Come hungry!
Tasty thai food in a comfortable upscale setting. You regularly see the chef / owner checking on each customer. Fresh ingredients and traditional flavors. Highly recommended.
Homemade Dutch style pancakes - savory or sweet. Recommend the mushroom for vegetarians. Nice to sit outside, but don't forget to see the cool interior.
Amazing museum nicely restored. Dutch Masters and famous Rembrandt on top floor.
Gorgeous old hotel property, several hundred years old. Retains many old architecture elements, but is infused with modern Picasso style art, frosted glass and modern furniture.
Ambiance and interior make this a great place for a special occasion dinner. Recommend: lobster rolls and Har Gow. Give yourself plenty of time for the experience.
Upscale, trendy, farm fresh, organic. Words that describe a terrific meal and setting. Worth the price for special occasions.
Nice interior and good mint tea. Otherwise skip this place -  food is not great. Would make a nice stop after drinking late night if the prices were about 3 euros lower per main item.
Nice walk and running path.. Part of the Greenway system. Great views of the Hudson River.
America's oldest Inn.. Great location to eat outside on the front porch and enjoy the garden. Decent food... Come here for the ambiance and history... Not the cuisine.
Good coffee, recommend the cookies, and fine chocolates.  Very cute shop and you can find some hard to get candy, and homemade caramels and chocolates.
Romantic and fun way to spend a summer evening. Cruise is about 90 minutes, heads up from Battery Park past World Trade Center, circles back past Statue of Liberty and back to dock. Cash bar.
Great Happy Hour specials. Prefer the oysters over the clams, for a hot side dish, lobster roll and old Bay fries very tasty. Mac and cheese looked delicious, but tasted a bit bland.
I love walking the old streets, looking at the colorful buildings, and the soft light in the summer evenings. Music may come around any corner so walk, explore and enjoy.
Chelsea location of this nyc coffee chain.  Recommend: the chocolate coconut balls and cold brew coffee.
Great outside cafe to enjoy a pizza, glass of wine, and salad or dessert. Recommend: Margherita pizza (tip.. Add artichokes) and the Caprese Salad.
Great studio space hidden among the furniture stores in Chelsea. Exhibits rotate frequently so come by often.
Good for cupcakes and sweet treats. Cupcakes are small for $3.50 but the frosting is high quality.
Yummy rich food make a nice brunch. Sit outside if possible. Recommend: sorbet mimosa, bone marrow, pecan sticky buns, shrimp and grits. Crab cakes are ok, but shells inside were not.
Great option here... Skip the mains and get a bunch of appetizers. Oysters, coconut curry clams, cucumber and feta salad. Great service. Try the Rosemary lemonade.

formattedAddress: 1200 New Hampshire Ave NW (M St. NW)

tip.text: Plenty of benches in both sun and shade make this a great lunch hour stop over.
One of the largest and nicest Starbucks I have been too. Clean and comfortable... But good luck getting inside.. The door is in a weird place past the subway stairs on 6th Ave.

formattedAddress: 32 Avenue of the Americas (at Walker St)

tip.text: Decent sichaun restaurant in Hells Kitchen. Recommend the large spicy boneless fish filet, tofu, vegetable stew, with garlic green snow pea tips on the side.
Cuban food restaurant was disappointing. Recommend the service and seafood stew, but pepper steak was not good. Overcooked stewed steak left it chewy and not tasty. Black beans are ok.

location.address: Ave. Isla Verde, Anexo Club Gallistico
formattedAddress: Ave. Isla Verde, Anexo Club Gallistico

tip.text: Love this place! Super fresh ceviche with tart lime juice bite without being overpowering. Seafood paella is a nice accompaniment, or the calamari starter. Good with a cold Medalla Light.
Classic beach hotel and Casino on Isle Verde strip. Love the pool, indoor/outdoor bar and beach front access. Skip the breakfast - better off at Dennys or Starbucks a few doors down.
Yummy ceviche unfortunately served with mufongo chips which are too thick and take away from delicate flavors. Mahi ceviche is spicy. Nice music and good service make a nice dinner spot.
Great sandwiches! Recommend: Tango with chickpeas and Vera with greens. Also get a ginger lemonade, refreshing natural ingredients is terrific to cool off from the sun.
Yummy local bake and bread cafe with decent coffee, nicely medium roasted. Get the goat cheese seasonal fruit cookie.. Mine had rhubarb and was surprisingly good.
Good food and interesting venue with modern art leaning against the walls. Good vegetarian options that offer modern take on Chinese fusion food. Recommend:tempura vegetable with orange citrus.
Interesting concept in vegetarian dining. $30 for seven courses. Food presentation was nice, but flavor and quality was not as good. Not sure it's worth the price.
Great coffee from quality local roasters. Recommend: the hand pour filter with foam milk on side. Recommend: lemon merengue pie for sweet and zesty snack.
Nice coffee outpost near the Wheelock escalator entrance. Lots of seating.  Coffee and food is good.. Not great.
Good pasteries and decent coffee... But nothing unique. This location good to sit outside and people watch outside Raffles City and City Hall MRT.
Amazing resort on a beautiful beach with a very nice beachfront restaurant. Easy to sit here for hours and enjoy a Lime Juice Soda water and the sea breeze.
Some nice Indian vegetarian dishes.. Recommend sambal and bread.
Nice beach with historic temple
Terrific park.. Live music, artists, literary enthusiasts, chess players... A great mix of New York City.

formattedAddress: W 4th St (btwn MacDougal St & University Pl)

tip.text: Fresh eats with good ingredients in a causal atmosphere. Try one of the fresh squeezed juice combinations instead of your usual beverage. Good for vegetarians.
Chain in airport location, service is efficient. Recommend the the chocolate muffin over the raisin scone and flat white is ok but not that creamy.
Young trendy crowd at this casual Italian pasta place. Reasonable price and good quantity. Good for friends or date.
Really serious coffee - filter, cold press, expresso work several organic beans for each. Definitely come here.
Nice coffee and a good place to chat after some shopping. Communal tables let you easily make new friends as well. Coffee is strong but not burnt.
Best traditional ceviche out of 8 places tried. Mostly seafood with some tomato, onions and other. Sit inside instead of next to the pool, too many flies.
Amazing city... Must have been the equivalent of big metropolis of Mexico City back in its time.
One of the best beach clubs along the strip.   Drinks are better than the food.
Surprised by this small narrow restaurant, tucked on 34th street. Green curry with vegetarian duck was good, som tum and fried tofu appetizers were ok.
Go at night.. Nicely refinished and lively, or perfect for a nice stroll.
Nice baked goods.. Both savory and sweet available. Sweet scone has good texture.  Flat white is average, but even the double shot is not strong. New store open from Tuesday. Handsome staff!
Good modern Italian food in a relaxed atmosphere.
Wow! This place is good! Great Chinese food, farm to table, fun UWS atmosphere. Any dumpling is good, and Thai curry clams & mussels is spicy and tasty. Full bar. Drink: sangria.
Monster menu! If you are craving it... They probably serve it. Vegetarian panini on grilled ciabatta is good.
Easy fun neighborhood vibe...this  neighborhood has high intensity disco balls and cute dancing bartenders. Drinks $4
Lovely plant and arboretum feel. The air is really fresh.. You won't want to stop breathing it in.
Beautiful atrium property. I am not usually one to enjoy walking the hotel, but this is an exception. Try it both in daylight and at night... Different.. but both lovely experiences.
Cool vibe..good mimosa... Unfortunately Chinese food is not vegetarian, so pancakes / syrup is only hot breakfast. Good looking waiters and great service.
Terrific coffee espresso drinks. Robust flavor and good finish. Recommend: Piccolo Latte and carrot cake square. Served by very handsome and knowledgeable baristas.

location.address: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St
formattedAddress: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St

tip.text: Good coffee..great atmosphere. Flat white is very creamy. Cakes have good flavor but might be a bit dry. Recommend ginger and lemongrass cold tea.
Big bright open, fresh plants, fresh air... Love everything about T3 except for the huge queues.  Come early!!
What a great local place! Wine and beer on tap. A nice fresh fruity sangria.  Lovely staff makes this a great place for a chat, date, or a quick drink.
Cool local coffee shop, good vegetarian food, dark roast is mild when measured against others. Get a cookie: a brownie with a chocolate chip cookie baked on to it... Impossible to go wrong.
Super nice staff.. Make an appointment, they will cut you in line in front of all the walk ins.
Free and unique shows rotate on and out at FIT museum. Many come from their own collection.  Seeing their storage room must be an amazing experience.

items.firstName: Museum at the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT)

venue.name: Museum at the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT)

tip.text: Local brews... Everything from drip to cold brew to espresso/flat white. Try the scones and pop tarts.  Drip coffee strong roast with bit of afterbite.  Check out their curated Spotify play list.
Great building design.. A nice place to sit outside and people watch.
Very cool local art and coffee shop. Interesting furniture and casual vibe. Recommend: raisin scone. It's dense.. Not fluffy like buttermilk biscuit. Congress with cream / jam.
Nice staff, quick service but the melon milk tea a bit disappointing. Mostly u just taste cream.
Great bakery, coffee house with covered outdoor seating. Recommend: salted caramel and the chocolate hazelnut cupcakes.
Local cafe vibe with good beans and good looking baristas. Recommend: ethiopian.. Nice floral notes but not too earthy. Cake slice is tasty but a bit sweet.
Super fresh buffet for vegetarian hot pot. Lots of great mushroom and tofu combinations. Get the black sesame dessert.
Classy modern bar at the Fairmont with a nice cocktail list. Lots of unique ingredients make for some tasty drinks. Recommend cocktail: corpse #2
Modern clean cafe with decent bakery and coffee selection. Iced coffee was better than the flat white.
Cool vibe coffee house / cafe. Try to get a couch in the courtyard out the backdoor.  Recommend: the long black. Good after taste not too burnt.
Wow! So nice! Design, food, service,  pool table, video wall .. there is a spa, and a guy that takes laser fitting of your feet to make custom leather shoes that ship to your home. Amazing!
Super nice club atmosphere with no buffet lines, you order from menus like civilized travelers. Wifi is apparently powered by hamsters on a wheel, bring your own.
Great location near Times Square, interesting cocktails. But music and decor leave don't leave you feeling any specific mood about the place.
Smaller club space in west Hells Kitchen, good sound and lighting. Great place for smaller events.
Good place for business dinner, too loud for a date. Large portion Italian food, but service is lacking. Best items were desserts.. Try the cannoli.
Historical landmark in NYC, beautiful structure, Guttenberg Bible, and a sense of what a wealthy financier was like. After Morgan passed away, the Frick bought many pieces to add to their collection.
Local shop for The City Bakery opened just 5 days ago - amazing cookies! Don't miss them! Recommend the chocolate chip.
Nice location to sit and enjoy coffee.
More a mini cafe than a coffee shop, it has a good food menu and serves cocktails. Coffee seemed a bit watery and pan chocalat was average.
Tasty smooth pour over coffee, touch of New Orleans bite at the finish. Try the citrus fennel scone..Interesting.. can't decide if I liked it. This is a good quiet coffee stop near Times Square.
Excellent vibe, leather couches, lively clients, very handsome waiters. Recommend: chocolate croissant and the sweet potato latte.
Cool shop place in refurbished Nabisco bakery with restaurants, stores, craft shops and grocery.. Check out the original building metal etchings on the walls to see the history.
Good coffee and good location for sitting and chatting.  Free wifi, but seems limited with what sites you can actually reach.  Try their holiday desserts: recommend the black forest cake.
One of my favorite Shanghai hotels. Definitely get the breakfast. Exercise facility and spa is well equipped. Love the Xmas train set in the lobby.
Great lounge with good hot food selections, full bar, dark lighting to feel relaxed. Note: no flight boarding announcements so watch your time.

location.address: Level 6 (Departure Level), Terminal 1, Hong Kong International Airport (near Gate 1)
formattedAddress: Level 6 (Departure Level), Terminal 1, Hong Kong International Airport (near Gate 1)

tip.text: A favorite hidden place to get a nice cocktail. Eclectic decor, comfy pillows and couches make this a place to lounge, the owner is a lovely hostess. Recommend: The Q followed by chocolate tini.
Upscale traditional Chinese vegetarian food try the sour soup and mock pork and vegetables stuffed into sesame bread pockets.

venue.name: Kung Tak Lam Shanghai Vegetarian Cuisine 功德林上海素食

tip.text: Clean efficient airport.. Tip: as soon as you exit baggage claim stop at the express train ticket counter for the shortest queue on the fastest way into central.

contact.facebookName: Hong Kong International Airport 香港國際機場

venue.name: Hong Kong International Airport (HKG) (香港國際機場)

tip.text: Very cool eclectic lesbian bar that welcomes the boys too.  Excellent selection of cocktails, couches make for a fun conversation or relaxing atmosphere. Cash only. 6F.
Visit before December 31 and enjoy Xmas Doraemon style.
Christmas special vegetarian French Onion soup.. Get the croutons, cheese on top.. And add the garlicky focaccia on the side.

formattedAddress: #B1-61, Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Rd)

tip.text: Beautiful classic hotel, host to many weddings and movies. Take time to stroll the courtyards and hallways. Tip do it during the day... Then again at night for a different experience.
Grab a draft Asahi from the robot pour machine, carrot apple ginger soup, and sushi.  Good wifi.

location.crossStreet: 成田空港第1ターミナル4F | Narita Int'l Airport Terminal 1,4F
formattedAddress: 三里塚御料牧場1-1 (成田空港第1ターミナル4F | Narita Int'l Airport Terminal 1,4F)

venue.name: Delta Sky Club - Satellite 1 (デルタ・スカイクラブ - 第1サテライト)

tip.text: Very cozy but small club... Food choices slightly more limited than full sized clubs.. But a great space.. Quiet to get work done.
Good sashimi quality and good value for the money. Tried the fried banana for dessert and the age tofu for appetizer.
Nice accessible center to watch performances... Get out quick to  coat check, or wait for 30 minutes.
Great drinks.. Get the horchata brandy freeze,  boozy sweet and cool,  they go down easy.. So pace yourself. Good bar nibbles..
Great quality cocktails! One of better mixologist locations in NYC, cozy and warm location, but gets crowded quickly. Recommend the Mata Hari and the Sleeping Car.
Great staff, cool modern European design vibe. Coffee is good! a solid dark roast but not burnt.. Try apple cinnamon muffin..like a cross between an apple pie and cake souffle.. Yummy!
Yummy vegetarian and nice cozy atmosphere, black pepper saitan with Chinese broccoli was good.  They serve wine as well.
Lovely local cafe / bakery / coffee shop! Delicious bakery (including gluten free options), good coffee in big warm mugs, several vegetarian soups. Yum!
Very nice coffee in ultra local coffee shop.  Top notch cookies, good iced coffee stop on warm days.
Great local coffee house... Single origin farm of the day for coffee, delicious treats.. Try the pie! Free WiFi.
Terrific restaurant.. High recommendation.. Actual old catalan farm house, 12-hours cooked veal is terrific.
Cool concept and venue, vegetarian safe zone in jamon-filled Barcelona. Choose your own organic ingredients, they make salad/sandwich/rice bowl. Free WiFi.
Cool looking hotel restaurant with only ok food. Better restaurants nearby for a good meal. Octopus salad appetizer is not bad.
Directly across from front door of St Pauls, large seating area, but usually a wait for restrooms.

location.address: Unit 2, Juxon House, St Paul's Church Yard
formattedAddress: Unit 2, Juxon House, St Paul's Church Yard

tip.text: It's worth the 16 pounds to climb to the top. But the first sign.. 257 steps.. Is not to the top.. Just to the first level. Be prepared for a hike to make it all the way up.
Nice Starbucks location in terminal but no outlets to charge your phone.
Nice size cafe with leather chairs, bit worn after a busy day.. Cafe mocha is good.
Bring your walking shoes between terminal 1 and 2 if you are connecting from long haul to regional jets. Stop at the "eat place" in terminal 2 for fresh sandwiches, yogurt and juice/wine/beer.

venue.name: Adolfo Suárez Madrid-Barajas Airport (MAD) (Aeropuerto Adolfo Suárez Madrid-Barajas)

tip.text: Good shopping and food court with a modern vibe and trendy furniture - stop by Harrods (London) locations for take away food or shopping.

venue.name: Lisbon Humberto Delgado Airport (LIS) (Aeroporto Humberto Delgado)

tip.text: Coffee is good without bitter bite, walk to the back for seating on large leather sofas, oatmeal chocolate chip cookies are thin and tasty.
Nice museum space, check out the lower for the modern pop-up exhibits, and definitely enjoy a stop at the restaurant.. Good food and views of the Bosphorus.

formattedAddress: Kılıçali Paşa Mah. Meclis-i Mebusan Cad. Antrepo No:4 Karaköy
location.address: Kılıçali Paşa Mah. Meclis-i Mebusan Cad. Antrepo No:4 Karaköy

contact.facebookName: Istanbul Modern | Istanbul Museum of Modern Art

tip.text: Great place for modern meal... Shared 4 starters and two desserts... Sea bass /tomatoes was tasty as were the zucchini fritters.
Meze plate
Highly recommend the organic farm breakfast. Amazingly fresh food, but by far the best part is the history about the land, farmers and pigeons shared by the hotel owner.

location.address: Aydınlı Mah. Yavuz Sok. No:1 Göreme Merkez
formattedAddress: Aydınlı Mah. Yavuz Sok. No:1 Göreme Merkez

tip.text: Amazing flight from Kaan our pilot, highly recommend a trip, peaceful and exciting, the smoothness and quiet of the ride from Butterfly helps even people with fears of height.
Good selection of pasta, soup, Dutch cheese at dinner. Plus open wine, champagne, and top shelf liquor.
Great place for date or event. The food is unique, looks beautiful, but some dishes the Latin-Asian fusion worked better than others. Recommend the tofu, spicy and sweet.
Solid coffee not far from times square.. Drip house blend very smooth.
Commuter type club, not as nice as JFK, but functional.
Unexpected to even have sky club here.. Super compact.. Amazing carminere Chilean red wine
Beautiful food and restaurant, great place for an event. Overall taste of food,  while good, you can likely do better at more local kitchen without the beautiful surroundings.
Great price and Peruvian specialities.
Outside seating - the best of the ATL sky clubs.
Spinach salad

formattedAddress: Gate T6, Concourse T (at ATL Airport)

tip.text: Recently expanded this club has large amount of seating and a good bar.
